15 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 858.314 of Title 59, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. A wholesaler shall:
19 1. Disclose in writing to the homeowner, before the execution
20 of any contract or written agreement, his or her intent to assign or
21 sell his or her equitable interest in the residential real estate
22 for a higher price than what is offered to the homeowner;
23 2. Provide a prominent written disclosure to the homeowner in
24 all written contracts between the parties stating that the homeowner
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1075 Page 7

1 shou ld seek legal advice before signing any contract concerning his
2 or her home; and
3 3. Disclose in writing to the homeowner that the homeowner has
4 the right to cancel the contract without penalty within two (2)
5 business days after the execution of the contract.
6 B. A wholesaler shall not, directly or indirectly:
7 1. Act as an advisor or consultant, or in any other manner
8 representing that the wholesaler is acting on behalf of the
9 homeowner; or
10 2. Represent himself or herself as holding a certification or
11 license, or being a member of a licensed profession, without
12 possession of the certification or license.
13 C. The homeowner shall have the right to cancel the contract
14 without penalty within two (2) business days from the date of
15 execution of the contract.
16 D. The wholesaler shall be prohibited from placing any lien or
17 encumbrance on or otherwise clouding title of the property.
18 E. Any contract or agreement used by a wholesaler shall contain
19 the following:
20 1. The name, address, and telephone number of the wholesaler;
21 2. The address of the residence involved in the transaction;
22 3. The total consideration to be given by the wholesaler to the
23 homeowner;
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1075 Page 8

1 4. A complete description of the terms of payment or other
2 consideration including, but not limited to, any services of any
3 nature which the wholesaler represents he or she will perform for
4 the seller before or after the sale; and
5 5. The following notice shall appear on the contract in
6 immediate proximity to the space reserved for the seller’s signature
7 and shall be in at least twelve-point bold type if the contract is
8 typed or in capital letters if the contract is printed. The notice
9 shall contain the name of the wholesaler, the date and time by which
10 the contract shall be canceled, and the following language:
11 “NOTICE REQUIRED BY OKLAHOMA LAW: You may cancel this contract
12 at any time before midnight of ____________________ (Date).
13 __________________________ (Name of Wholesaler) or anyone working
14 for ______________________ (Name of Wholesaler) CANNOT ask you to
15 sign or have you sign any deed or any other document until your
16 right to cancel this contract has ended. See the attached notice of
17 cancellation form for an explanation of this right. You should
18 always consult an attorney or community organization before signing
19 any legal documents concerning your home. It is advisable that you
20 find your own attorney. The law requires this contract to contain
21 the entire agreement. You should not rely upon any other written or
22 oral agreement or promise.”
23 F. Failure to include any of the required disclosures under
24 this section shall render the contract invalid and unenforceable by
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1075 Page 9

1 the wholesaler and shall entitle the homeowner to any earnest money
2 deposit involved in the transaction. Any earnest money deposit or
3 security deposit by a wholesaler shall be kept in an escrow account
4 maintained in this state with a federally insured financial
5 institution. The homeowner may terminate the contract at any time
6 if the wholesaler fails to comply with the provisions of this
7 section.
8 G. The Oklahoma Real Estate Commission shall create, publish,
9 and provide on its website a notice of cancellation form, which
10 shall be included by the wholesaler with any contract. This form
11 shall be provided to the homeowner at no cost.
12 H. The Commission shall promulgate any rules necessary to
13 implement the provisions of this section.
14 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025."
